{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"lake-piano-sir","description":"## Why\nFor the map to be additive the two signers must write distinct, self-identifying keys.\n## What\nHave both sign call sites set an unsigned `data[\"kind\"]` on the `SIGNATURE` event\n(`plan-review`, `completion-verifier`) so reducer routing is robust and not dependent on\nstring-parsing the manifest. The kind stays cryptographically anchored because `manifest[0]`\nis still in the signed manifest; `data[\"kind\"]` is routing metadata only.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py` (`sign_plan_review`, `refresh_attestation`),\n`src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` (`_verdict_manifest` / completion signing), `signing.py`\nif a kind passthrough is needed.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Plan-review SIGNATURE events carry `data[\"kind\"]==\"plan-review\"`.\n- [ ] Completion SIGNATURE events carry `data[\"kind\"]==\"completion-verifier\"`.\n- [ ] `data[\"kind\"]` is NOT added to the signed canonical payload (no PAYLOAD_VERSION bump).\n- [ ] Drift-refresh re-sign preserves the same kind.","id":"2c2d-651d-8081-41c7","parent_id":"4702-a55c-7aeb-445a","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Signing call sites: stamp data[kind] on SIGNATURE events"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782782696921746001,"uuid":"8694c1e3-31b0-4f55-b170-0b574eee3ff6"}